<title>USA: Standard &amp; Poor's adds, to S&amp;P 500.</title>
<headline>Standard &amp; Poor's adds, to S&amp;P 500.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-07-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Standard &amp; Poor's Corp said Tuesday that as a result of mergers and spinoffs it was changing the composition of its index of 500 stocks. The company also said it was dropping the smallest company currently in the index.</p>
<p>It said it will add Anadarko Petroleum Corp to the S&amp;P 500, replacing Santa Fe Energy Resources, which is spinning off its 82.8 percent stake in Monterey Resources Inc.</p>
<p>General Instrument Corp will be replaced by NextLevel Sytems Inc, one of the three companies that will result from the split-up of General Instrument.</p>
<p>In addition, said S&amp;P, Apache Corp will replace Intergraph Corp on the 500 index.</p>
<p>S&amp;P said Intergraph had a market capitalization of $406.6 million on Monday, July 21, the smallest of all S&amp;P 500 stocks.</p>
